# 40  OPTIONS - IPEmotion RT

#### 40 OPTIONS - IPEmotion RT

#### 40.1 Logger

For IPEmotion RT some settings of the OPTIONS are different compared to IPEmotion. Plugins
are not included in the IPEmotion RT OPTIONS, but a separate section called LOGGER is avail-
able to configure some interface settings. On the ETHERNET interface you define the IP-
address to detect IPETRONIK X-modules.

Figure 40.1 - Logger - IPETRONIK X interfaces

It is possible to control a couple of operations through command XML files. One important func-
tion is the control data download to USB drives when connected to the logger. In the OPTIONS
you can activate the access restriction. When this function is enabled the logger will not transfer
any data automatically to a normal USB drive. At any case the logger accepts only USB drives
named as STICK.

Figure 40.6 - Logger - Options

To activate for example the data transfer, an user must have the command XML file installed on
the USB stick.

Figure 40.7 - Command XML examples

With the command XML other operations are also supported. If you like to do several operations
at the same time, you can combine different commands in one XML file. The examples are loc-
ated here:

With the setting of the optional LAN IP-address the user can detect the logger on a different IP-
address than the factory default one 192.168.236.1. This setting is practical to detect logger
when the LAN adapter of the computer cannot be changed to DHCP due to IT policies.

Figure 40.8 - Setting - Optional IP address

In the example below the DHCP functionality is deactivated and the LAN IP of the computer is
set to a fixed IP-address 192.150.0.1. The corresponding logger IP-address is adapted to
192.150.0.1. With this setting a connection logger detect process is working.

Figure 40.9 - Visibility of interfaces

In some applications the X-modules are operating in a different IP-address range from the fact-
ory default 192.169.232.xxx. With the setting of the optonal X-LINK IP-address a detect of the
X-modules on the ETH interfaces from different IP ranges is supported.
